The paper deals with scheduling tasks on multiple processors, which is a topic in distributed computing (cs.DC). The tasks are represented as a tree-shaped graph, which is a common data structure in algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also discusses the computational complexity of the problem, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The application area of matrix factorization suggests that the paper may also belong to numerical analysis (cs.NA) or probability (cs.PR). Finally, the paper proposes and evaluates several heuristics, which is a topic in control systems (cs.SY).
